<doc id="1058762" wikidata="Q3485597" url="?curid=1058762" title="Six Mile Lake (Alaska)">
<text>Six Mile Lake is a lake in southern Alaska between Lake Clark and Iliamna Lake. The Newhalen River drains Six Mile Lake into Iliamna Lake. The lake is about long and about 1 km (3/4 mile) wide. The city of Nondalton lies on the lake&#x27;s western shores.
